# Core Development Rules

## Project Identity
- Monorepo: `mcp-stack` — MCP servers + shared infrastructure
- Owner: Markus Binder
- Stack: TypeScript / Node.js / ES modules
- Runtime: Node.js 20+, target ES2022
- Module system: Node16 (not bundled — runs as Node directly)
- Test runner: Vitest
- Package manager: npm workspaces

## Architecture
See `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` for the full reference. Key points:
- `packages/core` — shared lib (`@mcp-stack/core`): logger, OAuth 2.1, cache, tool-helpers, audit
- `packages/centerdevice` — CenterDevice DMS MCP (46 tools)
- `packages/bidrento` — Bidrento property management MCP (40 tools)
- `deploy/` — nginx configs, systemd units, update script

## Build Order
Core MUST build before service packages:
```bash
npm run build -w packages/core
npm run build -w packages/centerdevice
npm run build -w packages/bidrento
```

## TypeScript Standards
- Strict mode always (enforced via `tsconfig.base.json`)
- Prefer interfaces over types; avoid enums, use `as const` objects
- Use named exports (exception: where MCP SDK expects default)
- Explicit return types on public functions
- No `any` — use `unknown` + type guards
- Prefer early returns over nested conditionals

## Style
- Lowercase-with-dashes for directories (e.g., `packages/centerdevice/`)
- camelCase for variables/functions, PascalCase for interfaces/classes
- Meaningful variable names — no abbreviations except `req`, `res`, `ctx`
- No leftover `console.log` — use `@mcp-stack/core` logger

## Dependencies
- ALWAYS check `@mcp-stack/core` before adding external deps
- Core has zero external runtime deps for logger/cache; minimal for OAuth
- Pin exact versions in package.json
- Audit before adding: check last publish date, downloads, issues

## Error Handling
- Every async call gets try/catch
- Log errors with structured context via core logger
- Return structured error objects to Claude: `{ error: string, code?: string }`
- Never throw unhandled — catch and return MCP-compatible errors

## Execution Principles
- SEARCH FIRST: Check existing codebase for similar patterns
- REUSE FIRST: Extend `@mcp-stack/core` before creating new utilities
- MINIMAL CHANGES: Smallest diff that solves the problem
- VERIFY: `npm run build` and `npm test` must pass
- ASK, DON'T ASSUME: If requirements are ambiguous, ask
